1
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:15,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:36,620 --> 00:01:39,970
[Moonlight]

3
00:01:40,140 --> 00:01:43,000
[Episode 2]

4
00:01:48,110 --> 00:01:49,150
Who is that?

5
00:01:50,150 --> 00:01:50,940
[Hi.]

6
00:01:50,940 --> 00:01:52,310
[Are you Mr Zhou Chuan?]

7
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:55,300
[I'm Chu Li, the editor of
Yuan Yue Books.]

8
00:01:55,620 --> 00:01:56,759
[Here's the thing.]

9
00:01:56,780 --> 00:01:58,430
[I sent you a message yesterday.]

10
00:01:58,430 --> 00:01:59,950
[But you didn't reply to it.]

11
00:02:00,039 --> 00:02:02,280
[That's why I came to find you.]

12
00:02:03,030 --> 00:02:04,620
[Why her?]

13
00:02:04,789 --> 00:02:06,270
Our deputy editor wants me

14
00:02:06,270 --> 00:02:09,090
to talk to you about
the new book contract.

15
00:02:10,440 --> 00:02:11,390
Zhou Chuan doesn't live here.

16
00:02:11,390 --> 00:02:12,500
You got the wrong person.

17
00:02:18,320 --> 00:02:19,750
I got the wrong person?

18
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:26,050
It's 2070 though.

19
00:02:27,230 --> 00:02:29,790
Could there be two houses
numbered 2070 here?

20
00:02:29,420 --> 00:02:34,480
[Zhou Chuan]

21
00:02:34,820 --> 00:02:36,470
Zhou Chuan.

22
00:02:50,110 --> 00:02:50,510
Who is that?

23
00:02:50,510 --> 00:02:52,030
[Are you Mr Zhou Chuan?]

24
00:02:52,030 --> 00:02:54,910
Here's an important parcel
that needs your signature.

25
00:02:54,910 --> 00:02:56,220
What parcel?

26
00:02:57,590 --> 00:02:59,750
Are you really Mr Zhou Chuan?

27
00:03:02,230 --> 00:03:03,760
You deceived me!

28
00:03:03,990 --> 00:03:04,750
No.

29
00:03:04,750 --> 00:03:06,350
I'm truly sorry, Mr Zhou Chuan.

30
00:03:06,350 --> 00:03:08,030
For talking to you like this.

31
00:03:08,030 --> 00:03:09,310
I was left with no choice.

32
00:03:09,310 --> 00:03:11,260
If I don't see you today, I need to...

33
00:03:11,320 --> 00:03:12,510
Scram!

34
00:03:19,470 --> 00:03:20,990
Hello, is this management department?

35
00:03:21,420 --> 00:03:23,350
Mr Zhou, I'm really not a con artist.

36
00:03:23,350 --> 00:03:24,750
I can explain.

37
00:03:24,750 --> 00:03:25,790
Mr Zhou Chuan.

38
00:03:25,790 --> 00:03:27,310
Mr Zhou Chuan, open the door, please.

39
00:03:27,310 --> 00:03:28,900
Hurry up, she's over here!

40
00:03:30,350 --> 00:03:31,510
The owner complained that
you're disturbing the residents.

41
00:03:31,510 --> 00:03:32,590
Please leave immediately.

42
00:03:32,829 --> 00:03:34,350
I'm not disturbing the residents.

43
00:03:34,350 --> 00:03:35,190
Sirs.

44
00:03:35,190 --> 00:03:36,510
Is there any misunderstanding?

45
00:03:36,510 --> 00:03:38,070
I'm here for a business talk.

46
00:03:38,070 --> 00:03:39,150
Since you don't want to leave,

47
00:03:39,240 --> 00:03:40,420
we're left with no choice.

48
00:03:40,750 --> 00:03:42,640
Gentlemen, let's have a good talk!

49
00:03:42,640 --> 00:03:44,350
Brothers, we can have a good talk!

50
00:03:44,350 --> 00:03:45,520
Let go of me!

51
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:46,840
Gentlemen, you're so strong.

52
00:03:46,940 --> 00:03:47,860
I know Ms Gu!

53
00:03:47,860 --> 00:03:49,500
Wait a minute!

54
00:03:49,710 --> 00:03:50,470
Ms Gu.

55
00:03:50,470 --> 00:03:51,390
Do you still remember me?

56
00:03:51,480 --> 00:03:53,990
We met during your visit to
Yuan Yue Publishing House.

57
00:03:53,990 --> 00:03:54,990
Indeed.

58
00:03:54,990 --> 00:03:57,040
You even embarrassed me
in front of everyone.

59
00:04:01,710 --> 00:04:03,470
I know this girl. Let her go.

60
00:04:05,750 --> 00:04:07,150
It's okay, you may leave now.

61
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:12,100
Thank you, Ms Gu.

62
00:04:12,360 --> 00:04:14,340
I thought you're smart.

63
00:04:15,410 --> 00:04:19,010
As a girl, you should remain decent.

64
00:04:22,390 --> 00:04:24,810
Since Zhou Chuan refuses to show himself,
you won't get to see him.

65
00:04:25,070 --> 00:04:26,149
You should get going.

66
00:04:33,330 --> 00:04:34,920
Had you signed the new book contract
with Xin Dun Books earlier,

67
00:04:34,920 --> 00:04:36,590
you'd have been living in peace, right?

68
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,640
You're full of perseverance indeed.

69
00:04:38,640 --> 00:04:40,820
You came to find me right after
being transferred from Beijing.

70
00:04:41,550 --> 00:04:42,840
How much pressure does Xin Dun Books

71
00:04:42,840 --> 00:04:44,920
put on you when it comes to the KPIs?

72
00:04:46,950 --> 00:04:47,870
I know.

73
00:04:47,870 --> 00:04:49,180
You refuse to sign
the contract with Xin Dun Books

74
00:04:49,280 --> 00:04:51,170
because you want to
see if there's any company

75
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:53,150
who can offer you a higher price.

76
00:04:53,150 --> 00:04:55,850
But I'd say Xin Dun Books
offers the best conditions.

77
00:04:56,409 --> 00:04:57,320
Does it?

78
00:04:57,830 --> 00:05:00,550
When I signed
the Oriental Beauty with you guys,

79
00:05:00,550 --> 00:05:02,110
I really didn't feel that way.

80
00:05:03,430 --> 00:05:06,110
This time, we don't plan to set
a minimum number of printed copies.

81
00:05:06,110 --> 00:05:07,400
Five million yuan.

82
00:05:07,490 --> 00:05:09,510
To buy the full copyright of the book.

83
00:05:10,070 --> 00:05:11,950
Well, that can save me a lot of trouble.

84
00:05:12,230 --> 00:05:14,400
But I'm afraid I will repeat
Jiang Yu Cheng's mistake.

85
00:05:15,230 --> 00:05:17,290
If you were to reject me because of this,

86
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:18,550
that'd be so irrational of you.

87
00:05:18,640 --> 00:05:20,120
I just want to sign the contract

88
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:21,830
with a more sympathetic editor.

89
00:05:22,560 --> 00:05:23,910
We have plenty of time.

90
00:05:23,910 --> 00:05:26,110
After all, I've moved to
this neighbourhood.

91
00:05:26,110 --> 00:05:28,660
You can contact me
once you've made up your mind.

92
00:05:29,430 --> 00:05:32,030
Can't you hire a maid to clean your house?

93
00:05:36,140 --> 00:05:37,520
Your bag.

94
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:44,970
Thank you, Mr Zhou Chuan.

95
00:05:46,270 --> 00:05:47,670
Though we live in the same neighbourhood,

96
00:05:47,670 --> 00:05:50,350
don't come and bother me.

97
00:05:50,530 --> 00:05:52,200
-Goodbye.
-Bye-bye.

98
00:05:57,920 --> 00:05:59,670
You're still here?

99
00:06:01,930 --> 00:06:03,940
Mr Zhou Chuan!

100
00:06:04,040 --> 00:06:06,630
Yuan Yue Publishing House
sincerely wants to work with you.

101
00:06:06,630 --> 00:06:07,710
Five minutes.

102
00:06:07,710 --> 00:06:08,760
No, two minutes!

103
00:06:08,760 --> 00:06:10,990
Just give me two minutes.

104
00:06:10,990 --> 00:06:12,790
Mr Zhou Chuan, why don't you

105
00:06:12,790 --> 00:06:14,190
have a listen to the contract conditions

106
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:15,740
before rejecting me?

107
00:06:16,190 --> 00:06:17,270
Mr Zhou Chuan.

108
00:06:17,270 --> 00:06:19,710
Mr Zhou Chuan, are you listening?

109
00:06:20,050 --> 00:06:21,190
Turn to the first page of the contract.

110
00:06:21,280 --> 00:06:23,090
Read out the amount.

111
00:06:26,550 --> 00:06:27,680
Forty thousand yuan.

112
00:06:39,510 --> 00:06:41,390
You can decide on the restaurant.

113
00:06:41,390 --> 00:06:42,560
I've been away for three years.

114
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:44,540
I seriously have no idea what's good here.

115
00:06:46,430 --> 00:06:48,320
All right, bye.

116
00:07:01,040 --> 00:07:02,159
Long time no see.

117
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:18,490
Why are you here?

118
00:07:24,070 --> 00:07:24,950
Here's the book you asked for.

119
00:07:24,950 --> 00:07:26,360
-Take it.
-Sure.

120
00:07:26,440 --> 00:07:27,490
I'm taking off.

121
00:07:29,470 --> 00:07:30,470
Well,

122
00:07:30,470 --> 00:07:32,390
can't you hire a maid to clean the house?

123
00:07:33,620 --> 00:07:36,080
Monstress said the same thing just now.

124
00:07:38,710 --> 00:07:39,909
I'm aware that she was here.

125
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:41,500
You bumped into each other?

126
00:07:41,980 --> 00:07:42,860
What a pity.

127
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:45,290
I didn't get to see
the mighty waves beating the shore.

128
00:07:45,530 --> 00:07:47,020
The mighty waves beating the shore?

129
00:07:47,159 --> 00:07:48,640
The waves would wash
your dead body ashore.

130
00:07:49,590 --> 00:07:50,590
I'll get going.

131
00:07:53,470 --> 00:07:56,720
[Yuan Yue Publishing House]

132
00:08:00,190 --> 00:08:02,300
Chief Editor Yu.

133
00:08:02,640 --> 00:08:04,400
I went to meet Mr Zhou Chuan.

134
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:06,430
But he's very dissatisfied
with our contract.

135
00:08:06,430 --> 00:08:09,290
Could we increase
the minimum number of printed copies?

136
00:08:09,920 --> 00:08:12,130
Do you know what is
a minimum number of printed copies?

137
00:08:14,150 --> 00:08:16,230
A minimum number of
printed copies is a figure

138
00:08:16,230 --> 00:08:17,670
given by the circulation department

139
00:08:17,670 --> 00:08:20,160
after a market analysis based on
the author's previous sales.

140
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:22,540
No one can simply change it.

141
00:08:25,190 --> 00:08:26,910
Well, I've got something on.
I'm taking off.

142
00:08:26,990 --> 00:08:29,840
You may see Mr Liang Chong Lang
from the circulation department.

143
00:08:29,990 --> 00:08:30,840
Sure.

144
00:08:30,840 --> 00:08:32,560
Thank you, Chief Editor Yu.

145
00:08:34,710 --> 00:08:35,800
The minimum amount is
three thousand copies.

146
00:08:35,880 --> 00:08:37,020
Not more than that.

147
00:08:37,110 --> 00:08:38,610
But the editors in charge...

148
00:08:38,610 --> 00:08:39,929
What do the editors know?

149
00:08:40,010 --> 00:08:40,990
Do they know the market?

150
00:08:41,070 --> 00:08:42,380
Do they know marketing?

151
00:08:42,549 --> 00:08:43,630
If they do,

152
00:08:43,630 --> 00:08:45,190
what did they hire me for?

153
00:08:45,440 --> 00:08:46,320
Listen.

154
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:48,320
This is the era of big data.

155
00:08:48,320 --> 00:08:50,280
We can calculate

156
00:08:50,280 --> 00:08:51,750
how many copies can an author sell.

157
00:08:51,850 --> 00:08:53,170
He's a new author.

158
00:08:53,190 --> 00:08:54,870
And you want to get him
eight thousand copies.

159
00:08:54,870 --> 00:08:56,510
Who gave you the confidence?

160
00:08:56,510 --> 00:08:57,640
What do we do if we don't sell them out?

161
00:08:57,640 --> 00:08:59,270
Paste them on the wall?

162
00:08:59,520 --> 00:09:00,470
Three thousand it is.

163
00:09:00,470 --> 00:09:01,790
We can't do more than that.

164
00:09:01,940 --> 00:09:02,630
Hey.

165
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:04,550
Mr Liang has made
himself clear, hasn't he?

166
00:09:04,740 --> 00:09:06,590
-Hurry, go ahead.
-I'm going ahead.

167
00:09:07,780 --> 00:09:08,750
You get back here.

168
00:09:08,880 --> 00:09:09,680
Keep an eye on him.

169
00:09:09,680 --> 00:09:10,760
Don't let him stir up trouble.

170
00:09:10,760 --> 00:09:11,880
Just leave it to me.

171
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:20,950
Come in.

172
00:09:22,230 --> 00:09:23,420
Hello, Mr Liang.

173
00:09:23,520 --> 00:09:24,960
I'm Chu Li from the second section.

174
00:09:24,960 --> 00:09:26,200
And I'd like to ask you to increase

175
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:28,520
the minimum number of printed copies of
Mr Zhou Chuan's new book.

176
00:09:28,520 --> 00:09:31,360
Here's some data reports
about him that I came up with.

177
00:09:37,430 --> 00:09:38,310
[Zhou Chuan Data Reports]

178
00:09:39,800 --> 00:09:40,920
If I remember correctly,

179
00:09:40,920 --> 00:09:43,680
I've decided on his minimum number
of printed copies long ago.

180
00:09:43,680 --> 00:09:44,790
Right?

181
00:09:45,590 --> 00:09:48,000
If that's the case,
why are you here to find me?

182
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:50,240
Are you doubtful about my decision?

183
00:09:50,640 --> 00:09:52,120
Or do you think you did

184
00:09:52,120 --> 00:09:53,700
better homework than me?

185
00:09:53,950 --> 00:09:55,030
Listen.

186
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:57,440
Zhou Chuan's minimum number of
printed copies cannot be changed.

187
00:09:57,440 --> 00:09:59,360
If you can't get him sign the contract,
that's useless of you.

188
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:02,480
There are some in the editorial department
who have had contracts with great authors

189
00:10:02,480 --> 00:10:04,070
with a lowest number of printed copies.

190
00:10:04,070 --> 00:10:05,610
For example, Miao.

191
00:10:05,770 --> 00:10:07,130
Can you learn from them?

192
00:10:07,270 --> 00:10:08,320
Get out!

193
00:10:19,850 --> 00:10:20,730
[The Shadow Killer]

194
00:10:20,730 --> 00:10:22,230
[The Disappearing Zoo]

195
00:10:36,440 --> 00:10:38,290
[The Disappearing Zoo]

196
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:41,000
Mr Luo.

197
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,160
Ms Gu.

198
00:10:42,160 --> 00:10:43,220
Are you busy?

199
00:10:43,320 --> 00:10:44,520
Not at all.

200
00:10:44,670 --> 00:10:46,050
Let me tell you something.

201
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:48,560
Mr Li Yu would like to purchase
the right to Jiang Yu Cheng's

202
00:10:48,560 --> 00:10:49,510
The Disappearing Zoo.

203
00:10:49,510 --> 00:10:51,650
He gave a call to the big boss.

204
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:52,960
Li Yu?

205
00:10:53,150 --> 00:10:54,030
That's right.

206
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:57,640
You've been nurturing
Jiang Yu Cheng after all.

207
00:10:57,640 --> 00:11:00,110
It shouldn't be a problem
to leave it to you, right?

208
00:11:05,610 --> 00:11:06,630
Xiao Niao.

209
00:11:06,790 --> 00:11:09,050
How's your negotiation with
Jiang Yu Cheng going?

210
00:11:09,160 --> 00:11:10,920
I've asked my uncle to contact him.

211
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:13,200
We should hear from him very soon.

212
00:11:13,700 --> 00:11:14,800
Great.

213
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:18,450
Jiang Yu Cheng is much
easy than Zhou Chuan.

214
00:11:18,550 --> 00:11:20,630
I'm doing this

215
00:11:21,120 --> 00:11:23,880
because I hope you can seal the contract

216
00:11:23,880 --> 00:11:25,480
before Chu Li does.

217
00:11:26,280 --> 00:11:27,730
Therefore, you need to work hard.

218
00:11:28,350 --> 00:11:29,230
Got it.

219
00:11:29,230 --> 00:11:30,240
Thank you, Chief Editor Miao.

220
00:11:30,240 --> 00:11:31,410
It's Deputy Editor.

221
00:11:31,760 --> 00:11:32,730
Get back to your work.

222
00:11:36,820 --> 00:11:38,150
Deputy Editor Miao.

223
00:11:38,250 --> 00:11:40,100
I bought you this coffee.

224
00:11:40,120 --> 00:11:42,080
I don't know if it's
your favourite flavour.

225
00:11:42,080 --> 00:11:44,810
If you don't like it,
I can go get another one.

226
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:47,010
Sure, thank you.

227
00:11:48,200 --> 00:11:50,520
I heard that you met Zhou Chuan.

228
00:11:50,520 --> 00:11:51,830
How's the negotiation going?

229
00:11:53,220 --> 00:11:55,890
I didn't even have the chance to

230
00:11:55,990 --> 00:11:59,070
to hand the contract to him
and have it thrown at my face.

231
00:11:59,640 --> 00:12:01,710
Is it because you're
not good at negotiating?

232
00:12:02,350 --> 00:12:03,800
Mr Liang told me

233
00:12:03,800 --> 00:12:06,400
to ask you about negotiation techniques.

234
00:12:06,640 --> 00:12:08,920
Deputy Editor Miao,
how did you manage the negotiation?

235
00:12:08,920 --> 00:12:11,040
How did you decide on the figure?

236
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:12,120
All right.

237
00:12:13,240 --> 00:12:14,720
Let me ask you something, Chu Li.

238
00:12:14,860 --> 00:12:16,460
How many

239
00:12:16,560 --> 00:12:19,030
minimum copies do you
think we should give him?

240
00:12:19,640 --> 00:12:20,820
One hundred thousand.

241
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,680
The first royalty for an author

242
00:12:23,680 --> 00:12:26,030
is determined by the minimum
number of printed copies.

243
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:28,600
If he manages to receive a royalty of 15%,

244
00:12:28,800 --> 00:12:30,650
that's impressive enough.

245
00:12:30,650 --> 00:12:32,480
The figure he receives

246
00:12:32,480 --> 00:12:34,590
is determined by the cost that I can bear.

247
00:12:34,590 --> 00:12:36,630
We're running a publishing house here.

248
00:12:36,730 --> 00:12:38,090
Our boss is a businessman.

249
00:12:38,110 --> 00:12:40,080
And he needs to make money.

250
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:41,080
Zhou Chuan.

251
00:12:41,440 --> 00:12:43,600
He's got only one best-selling book.

252
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:45,560
Whether his next book is good or bad,

253
00:12:45,560 --> 00:12:46,490
how his writing is,

254
00:12:46,490 --> 00:12:47,840
none of us has a clue.

255
00:12:48,040 --> 00:12:49,680
In our industry,

256
00:12:49,680 --> 00:12:51,110
successful debut authors

257
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:52,660
can be found everywhere.

258
00:12:52,880 --> 00:12:55,760
And when it comes to ordinary authors,

259
00:12:55,760 --> 00:12:57,280
our publishing house offers

260
00:12:57,410 --> 00:12:59,390
three to five thousand yuan.

261
00:12:59,400 --> 00:13:00,720
But we paid Zhou Chuan

262
00:13:00,720 --> 00:13:02,800
thirty thousand yuan
for his first payment.

263
00:13:02,800 --> 00:13:04,480
And we increased it
to forty thousand yuan.

264
00:13:04,480 --> 00:13:05,970
It's enough to prove

265
00:13:05,970 --> 00:13:07,290
that our publishing house

266
00:13:07,290 --> 00:13:09,060
has a very high regard for him.

267
00:13:10,160 --> 00:13:11,230
But

268
00:13:11,320 --> 00:13:14,240
if I were to tell Mr Zhou Chuan this,

269
00:13:14,240 --> 00:13:15,840
I'm afraid he'd beat me up

270
00:13:15,930 --> 00:13:18,640
and send my body back here
through cash on delivery.

271
00:13:20,070 --> 00:13:22,710
And we wouldn't pay for that.

272
00:13:22,800 --> 00:13:25,010
Are you really an idiot?

273
00:13:25,080 --> 00:13:29,320
This conversation is between you and me.

274
00:13:29,480 --> 00:13:31,800
How you're going to deliver
the message to Zhou Chuan,

275
00:13:31,800 --> 00:13:34,080
that has to do with
your communication skills.

276
00:13:40,350 --> 00:13:43,340
[Zhou Chuan, Author: Something happened
and I'm not happy about it.]

277
00:13:43,340 --> 00:13:45,920
[When I'm angry, I can't help but wonder]

278
00:13:45,160 --> 00:13:47,640
Is the Zhou Chuan on Weibo

279
00:13:45,920 --> 00:13:50,210
[if I'm being mistreated
because I don't work hard enough.]

280
00:13:47,640 --> 00:13:50,210
the same as the one I met
during the daytime?

281
00:13:50,210 --> 00:13:52,560
[Perhaps I still need to
keep working hard]

282
00:13:50,380 --> 00:13:52,410
What gentle positive energy?

283
00:13:52,490 --> 00:13:54,410
He's simply a con man.

284
00:13:52,560 --> 00:13:55,130
[so as to earn
the respect that I deserve.]

285
00:14:15,950 --> 00:14:23,290
[The Navy Hired by the Monkey]

286
00:14:17,050 --> 00:14:19,580
[I can't help complaining
about an author.]

287
00:14:19,680 --> 00:14:20,720
[He's being all adorable on Weibo.]

288
00:14:20,720 --> 00:14:22,400
[But he's secretly a hot-tempered man.]

289
00:14:23,780 --> 00:14:26,330
[Zhou Chuan, Author:
The buns taste so bad today.]

290
00:14:26,330 --> 00:14:28,050
[Alas, I miss the hometown's meat bun.]

291
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:30,360
[Mr Zhou Chuan's dog is called Er Gou.]

292
00:14:28,130 --> 00:14:33,940
[Zhou Chuan, Author: My Er Gou]

293
00:14:32,800 --> 00:14:36,380
Zhou Chuan has to go abroad
for every New Year.

294
00:14:36,480 --> 00:14:39,570
But her dad celebrates it
in his hometown.

295
00:14:39,710 --> 00:14:41,180
That means

296
00:14:41,280 --> 00:14:42,720
it's been seven years

297
00:14:42,720 --> 00:14:44,890
since Zhou Chuan had
a meat bun from his hometown.

298
00:14:55,590 --> 00:15:03,070
[The Disappearing Mr Fox]

299
00:14:56,330 --> 00:14:58,560
[People pretend to be nice on Weibo.]

300
00:14:58,720 --> 00:15:00,120
[Someone made me so angry today.]

301
00:15:00,120 --> 00:15:01,660
[Even breathing makes me mad.]

302
00:15:01,750 --> 00:15:03,830
[And I can't do my work well.]

303
00:15:04,210 --> 00:15:07,250
Unexpectedly, this fox has a career.

304
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:15,600
Hello, Dad.

305
00:15:15,700 --> 00:15:18,270
I figured out you should be off work.

306
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:21,040
[How did you know I just arrived home?]

307
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:23,760
It's been only a few days.

308
00:15:23,850 --> 00:15:25,640
Why does it seem that
you've gained weight?

309
00:15:25,880 --> 00:15:27,320
Why do you have a double chin?

310
00:15:27,320 --> 00:15:28,840
Seriously? Have I gained weight?

311
00:15:28,840 --> 00:15:30,240
It's probably due to the angle.

312
00:15:30,240 --> 00:15:32,170
How about this? Do I look fat still?

313
00:15:35,010 --> 00:15:36,210
How's it going?

314
00:15:36,380 --> 00:15:37,650
How's your house hunting going?

315
00:15:37,760 --> 00:15:38,990
Is the money enough?

316
00:15:39,130 --> 00:15:42,260
It's enough. Don't worry, Dad.

317
00:15:42,400 --> 00:15:45,290
[Are you at your living place?]

318
00:15:45,400 --> 00:15:46,450
Make a turn.

319
00:15:46,560 --> 00:15:48,370
Let me check out the house.

320
00:15:48,830 --> 00:15:50,080
Sure.

321
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:56,760
Look, isn't it a nice living space?

322
00:15:56,880 --> 00:15:58,600
[The job is going well.]

323
00:15:58,610 --> 00:16:00,400
And the colleagues treat me very well.

324
00:16:00,400 --> 00:16:02,300
Don't you worry.

325
00:16:03,600 --> 00:16:06,160
Wait, why is it dark?

326
00:16:07,040 --> 00:16:08,360
What are you saying?

327
00:16:08,360 --> 00:16:09,410
It's a nice living place

328
00:16:09,410 --> 00:16:10,930
with a broken light.

329
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:13,570
Well, there's something
wrong with my phone.

330
00:16:13,570 --> 00:16:15,520
I'll get it repaired tomorrow.

331
00:16:16,020 --> 00:16:17,210
Your Highness.

332
00:16:17,210 --> 00:16:19,060
You're finally talking to me.

333
00:16:19,170 --> 00:16:20,790
You're not worth my time.

334
00:16:21,040 --> 00:16:22,120
Take it away.

335
00:16:24,640 --> 00:16:26,320
All right, I'm hanging up.

336
00:16:26,330 --> 00:16:27,280
Rest early.

337
00:16:27,280 --> 00:16:28,360
Bye-bye.

338
00:16:28,920 --> 00:16:30,530
Bye-bye. Miss you.

339
00:16:55,750 --> 00:16:56,660
[Lass.]

340
00:16:55,750 --> 00:16:59,970
[Dad]

341
00:16:56,760 --> 00:16:59,600
[I've transferred you some money.
Get yourself a new phone.]

342
00:16:59,620 --> 00:17:01,620
[You're all alone out there.
Take good care of yourself.]

343
00:17:01,720 --> 00:17:03,330
[Don't be so hard on yourself.]

344
00:17:19,589 --> 00:17:21,349
Auntie Zhang.

345
00:17:23,480 --> 00:17:26,280
You can't come to clean for this month?

346
00:17:28,220 --> 00:17:29,500
Sure, get well soon.

347
00:17:29,609 --> 00:17:30,690
Got it.

348
00:17:32,520 --> 00:17:34,000
Morning, Er Gou.

349
00:17:45,510 --> 00:17:47,000
Stop barking.

350
00:17:50,120 --> 00:17:51,390
[Er Gou.]

351
00:17:51,490 --> 00:17:52,760
Stop barking.

352
00:17:56,390 --> 00:17:57,420
Your house is not here.

353
00:17:57,530 --> 00:17:59,310
Let's go. It's the one behind here.

354
00:18:01,730 --> 00:18:03,120
Er Gou.

355
00:18:09,520 --> 00:18:11,790
It's really you, Mr Zhou Chuan.

356
00:18:11,920 --> 00:18:12,670
Mr Zhou Chuan.

357
00:18:12,750 --> 00:18:15,210
I'm sorry for keep bothering you.

358
00:18:17,680 --> 00:18:19,600
You're forgiven. Leave now.

359
00:18:19,700 --> 00:18:20,710
Come, Er Gou.

360
00:18:20,710 --> 00:18:22,510
Don't ever eat food given by strangers.

361
00:18:22,610 --> 00:18:23,490
Mr Zhou Chuan.

362
00:18:23,490 --> 00:18:25,370
These are the meat buns I bought

363
00:18:25,370 --> 00:18:27,170
from the hometown shop
you recommended online.

364
00:18:28,140 --> 00:18:29,390
Mr Zhou Chuan.

365
00:18:29,510 --> 00:18:30,780
Could we have a talk?

366
00:18:30,880 --> 00:18:31,990
No need.

367
00:18:32,090 --> 00:18:33,370
Er Gou and I have been on a diet.

368
00:18:33,470 --> 00:18:34,040
We're not eating them.

369
00:18:34,120 --> 00:18:35,970
Mr Zhou Chuan.

370
00:18:37,390 --> 00:18:38,970
Is your hand all right?

371
00:18:39,210 --> 00:18:40,850
It's okay.

372
00:18:40,950 --> 00:18:41,780
Mr Zhou Chuan.

373
00:18:41,880 --> 00:18:43,720
Could I have a minute of your time

374
00:18:43,720 --> 00:18:45,920
to talk about your new novel
and the figure on the contract?

375
00:18:45,920 --> 00:18:47,640
They're all negotiable.

376
00:19:08,440 --> 00:19:09,610
Thank you, Mr Zhou Chuan.

377
00:19:09,610 --> 00:19:10,650
Have a seat.

378
00:19:42,550 --> 00:19:44,750
You're Mr Zhou Chuan?

379
00:19:46,070 --> 00:19:48,250
And now you're calling me that.

380
00:19:49,600 --> 00:19:51,230
Mr Zhou Chuan.

381
00:19:51,310 --> 00:19:53,410
That was ignorant of me.

382
00:19:53,510 --> 00:19:55,520
Mr Zhou Chuan, please pardon me.

383
00:19:55,620 --> 00:19:56,980
Cut it out.

384
00:19:57,470 --> 00:19:59,180
You have only two minutes.

385
00:20:01,030 --> 00:20:02,130
I...

386
00:20:02,440 --> 00:20:03,360
Sir.

387
00:20:03,360 --> 00:20:05,390
It's bad for health to drink coffee
in the morning on an empty stomach.

388
00:20:05,470 --> 00:20:07,380
Have some bun first.

389
00:20:08,950 --> 00:20:09,610
Thanks.

390
00:20:09,610 --> 00:20:10,690
But I'd like to remind you

391
00:20:10,690 --> 00:20:13,980
that these buns don't worth as much as
the royalty of hundreds of thousands yuan.

392
00:20:15,210 --> 00:20:17,490
Though the minimum number of
printed copies is forty thousand,

393
00:20:17,490 --> 00:20:18,610
it's the highest figure
Yuan Yue Publishing House

394
00:20:18,610 --> 00:20:20,890
has had from the past two years.

395
00:20:20,890 --> 00:20:22,720
Our company is very sincere

396
00:20:22,720 --> 00:20:24,910
to you. The sun and the moon
are the witnesses.

397
00:20:25,010 --> 00:20:26,330
Then you go ask the sun and the moon

398
00:20:26,410 --> 00:20:28,650
if I deserve to be
humiliated by these figures.

399
00:20:28,790 --> 00:20:30,650
The sun and the moon are the witnesses?

400
00:20:31,080 --> 00:20:32,400
What have I done to deserve this?

401
00:20:32,490 --> 00:20:33,410
Mr Zhou Chuan.

402
00:20:33,410 --> 00:20:34,540
We're not humiliating you.

403
00:20:34,650 --> 00:20:35,570
I guarantee.

404
00:20:35,570 --> 00:20:36,890
If you sign the contract with us,

405
00:20:36,890 --> 00:20:39,330
I will definitely take care of
the publication of your book.

406
00:20:39,330 --> 00:20:40,580
We can even make it two hundred thousand,

407
00:20:40,670 --> 00:20:42,530
not to mention one hundred thousand.

408
00:20:42,620 --> 00:20:44,350
That's an empty promise.

409
00:20:44,630 --> 00:20:46,120
You could say whatever you want.

410
00:20:48,470 --> 00:20:49,770
Time's up.

411
00:20:49,770 --> 00:20:50,570
Thank you for your buns.

412
00:20:50,570 --> 00:20:52,400
Though mine isn't some cheap coffee.

413
00:20:53,480 --> 00:20:54,230
Mr Zhou Chuan.

414
00:20:54,310 --> 00:20:55,590
If I remember correctly,

415
00:20:55,680 --> 00:20:57,450
your Oriental Beauty

416
00:20:57,450 --> 00:20:59,330
has had three printings.

417
00:20:59,330 --> 00:21:00,360
Are you not confident

418
00:21:00,360 --> 00:21:02,090
with Book of Luo He?

419
00:21:02,940 --> 00:21:04,210
Are you trying to provoke me?

420
00:21:05,580 --> 00:21:08,000
Of course I'm confident with my work.

421
00:21:08,260 --> 00:21:09,670
Me too.

422
00:21:10,330 --> 00:21:12,230
It's just that Yuan Yue Publishing House
doesn't deserve it.

423
00:21:12,770 --> 00:21:13,970
In fact, you care not only

424
00:21:13,980 --> 00:21:15,350
the minimum number of printed copies.

425
00:21:15,430 --> 00:21:17,990
Otherwise, you'd have signed
the contract with Xin Dun Books.

426
00:21:19,490 --> 00:21:20,810
Cut it out.

427
00:21:20,890 --> 00:21:22,180
Please leave.

428
00:21:29,240 --> 00:21:32,190
[Time Is Like A Song]

429
00:21:33,930 --> 00:21:35,330
Yuan Yue Books is where Mr Zhou Gu Xuan

430
00:21:35,330 --> 00:21:36,930
created his sales miracle.

431
00:21:36,930 --> 00:21:39,730
Don't you want to surpass
your father in his battlefield

432
00:21:39,730 --> 00:21:41,290
and become the new miracle?

433
00:21:47,040 --> 00:21:47,890
I admit

434
00:21:47,990 --> 00:21:50,630
that Yuan Yue Publishing House's
conditions are of average.

435
00:21:50,720 --> 00:21:52,760
On the surface, you seem to be unwilling.

436
00:21:52,960 --> 00:21:55,050
But you've listened to
the contract contents for times.

437
00:21:55,050 --> 00:21:56,330
Actually, you're kind of

438
00:21:56,330 --> 00:21:58,980
interested in working with
Yuan Yue Books, right?

439
00:21:59,520 --> 00:22:00,710
You're a newbie, aren't you?

440
00:22:01,540 --> 00:22:03,300
You're so full of yourself.

441
00:22:05,050 --> 00:22:07,070
Yes, I'm a newbie.

442
00:22:07,150 --> 00:22:08,890
Naturally, I'm no match for

443
00:22:08,890 --> 00:22:10,330
those amazing editors.

444
00:22:10,330 --> 00:22:13,530
And you might find
what I'm saying all empty talk.

445
00:22:13,530 --> 00:22:14,440
But what I know is that,

446
00:22:14,520 --> 00:22:16,750
if I don't manage to sign the contract
and publish your book,

447
00:22:16,850 --> 00:22:19,570
there's no way I can stay at
the Yuan Yue Publishing House.

448
00:22:19,570 --> 00:22:21,330
So, compared to those amazing editors,

449
00:22:21,430 --> 00:22:24,080
I am more determined.

450
00:22:24,210 --> 00:22:25,950
Please, Mr Zhou Chuan.

451
00:22:26,050 --> 00:22:27,170
Please.

452
00:22:27,280 --> 00:22:30,130
Let's sign the contract.

453
00:22:32,430 --> 00:22:33,590
Are you done talking?

454
00:22:34,980 --> 00:22:36,300
Leave.

455
00:22:49,140 --> 00:22:50,650
Mr Zhou Chuan.

456
00:22:51,050 --> 00:22:52,300
This is my name card.

457
00:22:52,410 --> 00:22:54,040
If you ever change your mind,

458
00:22:54,050 --> 00:22:55,820
contact me anytime.

459
00:23:01,280 --> 00:23:03,000
[Chu Li, Literary Editor,
Phone, WeChat, Email, QQ]

460
00:23:02,220 --> 00:23:03,460
I'll put it here.

461
00:23:06,350 --> 00:23:07,750
I'm leaving.

462
00:23:25,010 --> 00:23:25,850
Let me give you a hand.

463
00:23:25,850 --> 00:23:27,450
Sure. Thank you.

464
00:23:27,450 --> 00:23:28,170
Okay.

465
00:23:28,270 --> 00:23:30,080
-Let me do it from here.
-Sure.

466
00:23:30,410 --> 00:23:31,710
Here.

467
00:23:38,090 --> 00:23:40,090
-Well, thank you.
-You're welcome.

468
00:23:45,160 --> 00:23:47,080
Is this your bookstore?

469
00:23:50,490 --> 00:23:51,760
Please come in if you want to buy books.

470
00:23:51,850 --> 00:23:53,330
Can't I have a tour?

471
00:23:55,630 --> 00:23:57,620
Well, help yourself.

472
00:23:58,010 --> 00:24:00,450
Someone wants to buy the right
to The Disappearing Zoo.

473
00:24:11,910 --> 00:24:13,940
Your bookstore is doing not bad.

474
00:24:15,130 --> 00:24:17,280
Thank you. Please take a seat.

475
00:24:29,580 --> 00:24:31,020
Let's get down to business.

476
00:24:32,420 --> 00:24:34,130
The agreement says that

477
00:24:34,350 --> 00:24:37,520
Xin Dun Books owns the right to
The Disappearing Series for ten years.

478
00:24:37,920 --> 00:24:41,010
And now Mr Li Yu has eyes for
The Disappearing Zoo,

479
00:24:41,010 --> 00:24:42,330
and wants to make it into a movie.

480
00:24:44,250 --> 00:24:46,140
It's a very good opportunity.

481
00:24:47,550 --> 00:24:48,650
What about you?

482
00:24:49,140 --> 00:24:52,050
What's your role in it?

483
00:24:52,520 --> 00:24:54,610
If you agree to sell the right,

484
00:24:54,820 --> 00:24:56,650
I will have a meeting with the director,

485
00:24:56,650 --> 00:25:00,580
the producers, and you.

486
00:25:01,850 --> 00:25:03,220
The original author must join it.

487
00:25:03,220 --> 00:25:04,860
That's the only request from the director.

488
00:25:07,700 --> 00:25:08,900
Then no need.

489
00:25:09,130 --> 00:25:10,380
I'm not selling the right.

490
00:25:11,400 --> 00:25:13,470
Do you have to avoid me?

491
00:25:15,050 --> 00:25:16,610
We're talking about Li Yu.

492
00:25:17,010 --> 00:25:19,300
There are many authors
who want to work with him.

493
00:25:21,870 --> 00:25:23,460
I'm not avoiding you.

494
00:25:24,250 --> 00:25:26,370
I just want to have
nothing to do with you.

495
00:25:30,060 --> 00:25:33,280
You don't always come across
this kind of opportunity, Jiang Yu Cheng.

496
00:25:34,850 --> 00:25:37,930
Do you want to hide here
running the bookstore forever?

497
00:25:47,770 --> 00:25:51,550
Did I get Mr Zhou Chuan wrong?

498
00:25:52,670 --> 00:25:55,970
How should I persuade him tomorrow?

499
00:25:59,580 --> 00:26:01,690
Xiao Bai, where's your boss?

500
00:26:01,690 --> 00:26:03,070
He left early today.

501
00:26:03,140 --> 00:26:05,040
I too have no idea where he went.

502
00:26:06,220 --> 00:26:07,370
Fine.

503
00:26:11,740 --> 00:26:19,850
[The Navy Hired by the Monkey]

504
00:26:13,960 --> 00:26:15,850
[It's another ugly rejection.]

505
00:26:15,950 --> 00:26:16,910
[I'd say that]

506
00:26:16,940 --> 00:26:19,900
[the dog of that author
is friendlier than him.]

507
00:26:19,850 --> 00:26:33,440
[The Disappearing Mr Fox]

508
00:26:20,460 --> 00:26:23,290
[I showed him my utmost sincerity]

509
00:26:23,290 --> 00:26:25,810
[and asked him to
sign a publishing contract.]

510
00:26:25,810 --> 00:26:28,730
[And it's the first time
I bought a man breakfast.]

511
00:26:28,730 --> 00:26:31,170
[He said it's not worth the royalty
of hundreds of thousands yuan.]

512
00:26:31,170 --> 00:26:32,740
[It's not about a bun.]

513
00:26:32,840 --> 00:26:35,440
[It's about my girly heart.]

514
00:26:33,440 --> 00:26:39,430
[The Navy Hired by the Monkey]

515
00:26:35,660 --> 00:26:37,080
Why does this experience

516
00:26:37,250 --> 00:26:39,510
seem so familiar?

517
00:26:51,220 --> 00:26:55,360
[Chu Li, Literary Editor,
Phone, WeChat, Email, QQ]

518
00:26:55,360 --> 00:26:56,720
[The Navy Hired by the Monkey]

519
00:27:00,860 --> 00:27:02,040
[Chu Li, Literary Editor
[The Navy Hired by the Monkey]

520
00:27:04,290 --> 00:27:06,530
[The Monkey is Chu Li?]

521
00:27:11,010 --> 00:27:12,760
Good morning.

522
00:27:12,860 --> 00:27:14,770
Welcome. It's you.

523
00:27:17,280 --> 00:27:19,220
Where's your copy of Time Is Like A Song?

524
00:27:19,310 --> 00:27:22,210
I remember it's placed
alongside Oriental Beauty.

525
00:27:22,210 --> 00:27:25,150
I want to compare them for something.

526
00:27:25,270 --> 00:27:26,620
We're going to change the display stand.

527
00:27:26,620 --> 00:27:28,850
You can go check them out
from the bookshelf behind there.

528
00:27:31,490 --> 00:27:32,600
Sure.

529
00:27:40,700 --> 00:27:43,240
[Wait, why am I avoiding her?]

530
00:27:43,970 --> 00:27:50,350
[The Disappearing Mr Fox]

531
00:27:43,990 --> 00:27:47,070
[Do you think I should
pay him a third visit?]

532
00:27:47,180 --> 00:27:50,840
[I'll buy him a more classy-looking congee
with pork and century egg tomorrow.]

533
00:28:14,330 --> 00:28:16,490
Mr Zhou Chuan.

534
00:28:22,940 --> 00:28:24,460
What a coincidence.

535
00:28:25,040 --> 00:28:26,320
I'll get going.

536
00:28:26,620 --> 00:28:28,250
Wait a minute.

537
00:28:28,470 --> 00:28:30,900
Mr Zhou Chuan,
I'm not trying to be a nagger.

538
00:28:30,990 --> 00:28:32,420
What I told you this morning,

539
00:28:32,430 --> 00:28:34,710
could you give it another thought?

540
00:28:37,270 --> 00:28:38,770
I'll give it some thought.

541
00:29:00,710 --> 00:29:01,550
Jiang Yu Cheng.

542
00:29:01,650 --> 00:29:02,840
Jiang...

